<node id="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d0">World Athletics Federation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">World Athletics Federation, also known as World Athletics, is the governing body responsible for overseeing various aspects of global track and field events. Its primary functions include organizing and managing the World Athletics Championship, which is one of the most prestigious international competitions in the sport.

One of the key roles of the World Athletics Federation is to validate athletic records, ensuring that performances meet the required standards and criteria. This process involves verifying the authenticity and accuracy of record-breaking feats, taking into account factors such as equipment used, course conditions, and other relevant details. The federation's scope extends beyond championship management and record validation; it also plays a crucial role in promoting global track and field events, fostering cooperation among member nations, and providing support for athletes through various programs and initiatives.

It is worth noting that the World Athletics Federation has undergone changes in its name and structure over time. However, its core functions and responsibilities remain unchanged, with a continued focus on enhancing the sport, protecting athlete welfare, and advancing global competition. The federation oversees record validations, including sprint records set at the championship, ensuring the accuracy of these performances. Its governing role encompasses both championship management and record validation processes, emphasizing its comprehensive involvement in the sport.

In summary, the World Athletics Federation is a pivotal organization in the track and field community, responsible for overseeing various aspects of global events, validating athletic records, promoting cooperation among member nations, and supporting athletes through various initiatives.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.</data>
