<node id="Interest Rates">
  <data key="d0">Interest Rates</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Interest rates refer to the interest on loans or savings accounts set by financial institutions.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest rates are a factor influencing market performance and regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest rates refer to the percentage at which commercial banks and other financial institutions lend money to customers, influencing borrowing costs and economic activity.`&lt;SEP&gt;Interest rates refer to the percentage at which commercial banks and other financial institutions lend money to customers, influencing borrowing costs and economic activity.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest rates refer to the rate at which banks lend money to customers.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest rates are a crucial economic factor influencing investor decisions and market performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0d3b88d3601a1081c8354e0ef27952f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0c6684aa00106f16e7869f519061642&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-996c8aba3ce4de0e9bb90c0d569231f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a83bcdf6e7b7269cfd17b4f21457de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f1e5469f6278ea8a34bff96b293b69</data>
