<edge source="C客戶" target="B人員">
  <data key="d7">15.0</data>
  <data key="d8">**Relation Summary: B人員 (B personnel) and C客戶 (Customer C)**

B人員, also referred to as Engineer B, is responsible for handling various aspects of customer maintenance for C客戶. Their primary role involves addressing ongoing maintenance needs, including system upkeep and troubleshooting issues that may arise. According to multiple descriptions, this includes not just resolving immediate problems but also maintaining a record of past work done on C客戶's systems.

Engineer B is directly responsible for handling the maintenance tasks assigned to them by customer C. This encompasses routine maintenance, as well as any ad-hoc repairs or adjustments needed. Their responsibilities are multifaceted and crucial in ensuring the optimal functioning of C客戶's systems. The personnel B is handling maintenance for customer C, with Engineer B Personnel being specifically responsible for maintaining C Customer's account.

The engineer B is also involved in handling specific issues that might come up during maintenance, while supporting C客戶 with ongoing maintenance issues. Furthermore, it has been noted that C客戶 relies on B人員 for ongoing maintenance and support, a critical aspect of customer satisfaction.

In summary, the role of Engineer B is to handle various tasks related to C Customer's maintenance, including routine upkeep, troubleshooting, and record-keeping. This position is essential in ensuring the smooth functioning of C Customer's systems.</data>
  <data key="d9">customer,customer handling,customer maintenance,customer relationship,customer support,customer-engineer,customer-engineer relationship,employee-customer,engineer handling,engineer responsibility,engineer role,engineer support,engineer-customer interaction,engineer-customer relationship,maintenance,maintenance issue,maintenance relationship,maintenance service,maintenance task</data>
